      "chapter": 1,
      "sanskrit": "Ahimsa paramo dharma",
      "transliteration": "",
      "text": "Non-violence is the supreme religion. All beings desire to live; none wish to die. Recognizing this, one who truly knows the Dhamma practices non-injury in thought, word, and deed toward all living beings.",
